<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

Provides named state channels as an abstraction over `$:/state/...` tiddlers. Views read and write logical channel names; the container widget manages the actual state tiddler paths internally. Reactive rules fire when channels change, enabling declarative state dependencies.

!! Features

* Named channels — views reference names like `selected-project`, not state tiddler paths
* Reactive rules — declarative wikitext actions fire when a channel changes
* Instance isolation — each `<$statewrap>` gets its own state namespace
* Re-entry guard — rules cannot cascade (prevents infinite loops)
* Filter operators — tree-dependent `[statewrap-get[channel]]` / `[statewrap-ref[channel]]` for in-scope use, and tree-independent `[<instid>statewrap-lookup[channel]]` for reading a channel's value from outside the `<$statewrap>` (e.g. in `\function` bodies or introspection tools)

!! Prerequisites

TiddlyWiki 5.3.0 or later.

!! Quick start

# Add `rimir/statewrap` to `tiddlywiki.info` plugins
# Restart server
# Use `<$statewrap>` in your tiddlers with channel definitions

